Name: catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia 1
Definition: A catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia that is characterized by autosomal dominant inheritance and has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the RYR2 gene on chromosome 1q43.

Name: catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia 2
Definition: A catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia that is characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the CASQ2 gene on chromosome 1p13.

Name: catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia 3
Definition: A catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia that is characterized by early onset mortality and has_material_basis_in variation in the chromosomal region 7p22-p14.

Name: catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia 4
Definition: A catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia that is characterized by autosomal dominant inheritance and has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the CALM1 gene on chromosome 14q32.

Name: catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia 5
Definition: A catecholaminergic polymorphic ventricular tachycardia that is characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance and has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the TRDN gene on chromosome 6q22.
